The rest of the surnames of the Italian Dukes are
these, viz. that of Parma is Fernese, signifying Partridges;
that of Modena is Astie, that of Florence de Medicis;
that of Vrbine, Francesco Maria, and the last Duke of Mantua,
Gonsaga; the Dutchy of Ferrara, being dissolved, is
converted to the Popes patrimony.

